President Muhammadu Buhari has joined the national leadership of the Christian Association of Nigeria and the Christian community in Nigeria in mourning the passing of the General Secretary of the Christian Association of Nigeria, Rev (Dr) Musa Asake.  The president's condolences were contained in a statement Friday by his spokesman, Mr Femi Adesina.  The president, while commiserating with the family of the late Reverend, prayed that God Almighty comfort all those morning the departed and grant his soul eternal rest.